prompt:
Look at the ComputeWithLogging function in Impure.calr. It logs and computes. Your task: create a new pure function called JustCompute that does only the computation (add a and b) WITHOUT any effects.

Create this pure function:
§F{f004:JustCompute:pub}
  §I{i32:a}
  §I{i32:b}
  §O{i32}
  §R (+ a b)
§/F{f004}

Notice: NO §E{} line! This function is pure - it only computes with no side effects. Calor makes purity explicit by requiring effect declarations only when effects are used.
